II. Spatio* objects

  1. I like Mercator, Van Der Grinten, Robinson because they are easy to visualize where part of the earth are.

  2. The two plots looks similar

  1. areas_proj <- sapply(sd_tracts_proj@polygons, function(x) x@area)

  2. The column ALAND provided in sd_tracts data provides kind of different area information than areas_proj. The discripancies between the areas is so large (see mean of differences below). The differences in units or how people measure the area and transform the data might effect this discripancies.

(areas_proj - as.numeric(sd_tracts@data$ALAND)) %>% mean
